<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,582,822]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,583,607]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H." box="[277,606,582,606]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="67 - 96" refId="ref14269" refString="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H. (2004) Taxonomic studies on the Talitridae (Crustacea, Amphipoda) from Taiwan. II. The genus Platorchestia. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 40, 67 - 96." type="journal article" year="2004">Miyamoto &amp; Morino (2004)</bibRefCitation>
established three groups within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1982" box="[986,1136,582,606]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Platorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[986,1136,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Platorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the presence or absence of sexually dimorphic characters. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1982" box="[628,778,619,643]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Platorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[628,778,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Platorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(group 2) is based on having a sexually dimorphic second antenna (incrassate) and no sexual dimorphism in pereopods 6 or 7. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H." box="[1109,1436,654,678]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="67 - 96" refId="ref14269" refString="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H. (2004) Taxonomic studies on the Talitridae (Crustacea, Amphipoda) from Taiwan. II. The genus Platorchestia. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 40, 67 - 96." type="journal article" year="2004">Miyamoto &amp; Morino (2004)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1982" box="[151,301,691,715]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Platorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,301,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Platorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(group 2) contains two species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Stock, 1996" authorityName="Stock" authorityYear="1996" box="[689,1021,690,715]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Platorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ashmoleorum">
<emphasis box="[689,873,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. ashmoleorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, J. H." box="[884,1021,690,714]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="149 - 157" refId="ref14597" refString="Stock, J. H. (1996) The genus Platorchestia (Crustacea, Amphipoda) on the Mid-Atlantic islands, with description of new species from Saint Helena. Miscel-laia. Zooloica, 19 (1), 149 - 157." type="journal article" year="1996">Stock, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mateus, Mateus &amp; Afonso, 1986)" baseAuthorityName="Mateus, Mateus &amp; Afonso" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Platorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodi">
<emphasis box="[1084,1200,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. monodi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mateus, A. &amp; Mateus, E. &amp; Afonso, O." pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="87 - 126" refId="ref14178" refString="Mateus, A., Mateus, E. &amp; Afonso, O. (1986) Amphipodes Littoraux et de l'interieur recueillis aux Acores pendant la Campagne &quot; Biacores &quot; (1971) sur le navire Jean Charcot. Anais da Faculdadede Ciencias do Porto, 65, 87 - 126." type="journal article" year="1986">Mateus, Mateus &amp; Afonso, 1986</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. There are additional species of this distinctive group in the Australian Museum collections from the western South-Pacific islands of 
<collectingCountry box="[522,564,762,786]" name="Fiji" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, Hawaii, 
<collectingCountry box="[671,741,763,787]" name="Tonga" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Tonga</collectingCountry>
and the new species 
<taxonomicName authority="Lowry, 2012" authorityName="Lowry" authorityYear="2012" box="[981,1078,763,787]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Platorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[981,1078,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. smithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1085,1176,763,787]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1085,1176,763,787]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, described below from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[237,343,798,822]" name="Australia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
